full_text:
Anyone else get &quot;ghost here&quot; as a greeting.  I just finished up a session just now, and heard &quot;ghost here&quot; for the second time.  Both times were crystal clear.

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Sumption &lt;purplealiengirl@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt;  Even when doing the test videos, I just announce out loud I&#39;m doing an EVP
&gt; recording. Even with these it&#39;s like they are right there and ready. There
&gt; seems to be some, or a group that actually transmit something, and
&gt; participants stand in front of, or use a mic of somekind. When I first
&gt; started, box #1, &quot;they&quot; had Lincoln, and were showing him how to use the
&gt; mic. Chicken skin just thinking about it!
&gt; 
&gt;  Like this one, starts out &quot;you don&#39;t believe&quot; sung, I think it&#39;s a
&gt; remodulated song from Radio Disney. I try to explain to them, I look in a
&gt; mirror, and that ain&#39;t alien Princess looking back! It&#39;s a difficult
&gt; concept. This was manual sweep with a minimal &quot;box&quot;.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;  Frank-S
&gt; 
&gt; On Sun, Oct 24, 2010 at 8:33 AM, Mvanah Maloti &lt;inyanga4@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;  [Attachment(s)&lt;https://mail.google.com/mail/?ui=2&view=js&name=main,tlist&ver=vDkaykVSG9w.en.&am=!yGvcqUNUUxexhZ5ijtQ2ZMKIZroesisZtoKH5kognAihF0mgsh4P&fri#12bdea83ffbe09fe_TopText&gt;from Mvanah Maloti included below]
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;   Tim,
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; I experience something similar on a regular basis.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; My &quot;crew&quot; usually begins immediately (sometimes less than 20 or 30 seconds
&gt; &gt; and often as soon as the box is turned on) with my name and the words *
&gt; &gt; &quot;START&quot;,* *&quot;Here&quot;* or *&quot;Hello&quot;* to show me that we&#39;ve made proper contact
&gt; &gt; and the connection is clear.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; The sessions typically end in much the same way with a loud* &quot;STOP!&quot;* or *
&gt; &gt; &quot;end&quot;* to signal that we&#39;re finished.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; I&#39;ve attached an example of my own and thank you for sharing!
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; It&#39;s incredibly interesting to read about and hear the communication
&gt; &gt; &quot;systems&quot; employed by other researchers.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; -Jerome
